{
  "texts": [
    "PRNet (Wang and Solomon, 2019b) uses confidence ranking for points, and selects point pairs with high confidence for SVD solution.",
    "Deep closest point (DCP) DCP (Wang and Solomon, 2019a) and DeepVCP (Lu et al., 2019b), the closest virtual point of depth, are calculated using the weighted confidence and the position of the point to solve the relative attitude.",
    "DGR (Choy et al., 2020) uses the weighted SVD to solve the rigid transform after passing the confidence selection point pair and retaining the confidence as the weight.",
    "If only the point pair is entered into the solver module of the SVD, this usually means giving up the confidence of the point pair.",
    "This also causes the need to use coordinate values for network backpropagation."
  ]
}